(1, 10, 27, 27, 'kjv', 'Hadoram, and Uzal, and Diklah,', 4, 34, 'connection', 'Lineage Significance', 'The names Hadoram, Uzal, and Diklah are part of the genealogical record that emphasizes the fulfillment of God''s promise to Noah to repopulate the earth (Genesis 9:1). These names contribute to the larger narrative of humanity''s spread and the establishment of nations, which is a recurring theme throughout Genesis.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Genesis 9:1", "description": "God commands Noah to be fruitful and multiply, linking to the genealogical context."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini');